  "summary": "## Summary: Create a local SQLite database to track all downloads with metadata\n\n### Changes Implemented\n- Created DownloadRecord model with full metadata (URL, platform, title, file path, size, status, timestamps)\n- Created DownloadDatabase helper with complete CRUD operations, search, filtering, and cleanup\n- Created DownloadHistoryProvider for state management with ChangeNotifier/Provider pattern\n- Created DownloadHistoryScreen with search bar, status filter chips, swipe-to-delete, retry for failed downloads, and clear history options\n- Provided integration instructions for main.dart (provider wrapper) and existing download logic hooks\n\n### Files Modified\n- `lib/models/download_record.dart` (NEW) — Data model with serialization, formatting helpers\n- `lib/database/download_database.dart` (NEW) — SQLite database helper with full CRUD, search, indexing\n- `lib/providers/download_history_provider.dart` (NEW) — State management layer\n- `lib/screens/download_history_screen.dart` (NEW) — Complete history UI screen\n- `pubspec.yaml` (MODIFY) — Add sqflite, path, intl, provider dependencies\n- `lib/main.dart` (MODIFY) — Wrap app with Provider\n\n### Notes for Developer\n- Standard file tools (Read/Write/Edit/Bash) were unavailable in this session; all code provided as copy-paste blocks\n- TODO markers placed at integration points: retry-download triggering, file opening, platform detection\n- Add `open_file` package if you want the \"open file\" button to work\n- Run `flutter pub get` after adding dependencies\n- Run `flutter analyze` to verify\n- The retry mechanism needs to be wired into your existing download service\n\n### Verification Status\n- Could not run Playwright verification because the standard Bash/Run tools are unavailable in this session\n- Code follows sqflite best practices from official documentation (context7 verified)\n- Manual verification recommended: run `flutter analyze` and test on device/emulator",
